## 🚀 1️⃣ Mise en œuvre de GitHub Actions pour CI/CD  
### 🔧 Configuration du pipeline automatisé

#### 1.1 Structure du `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
```yaml
name: Deploy Food Delivery App

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
    paths:
      - 'src/**'
      - 'docker/**'
      - 'package.json'
  pull_request:
    branches:
      - develop

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: 📦 Set up Node.js
        uses: actions/setup-node@v3
        with:
          node-version: 18.x
      - name: 🧹 Install dependencies
        run: npm ci
      - name: 🧪 Run tests
        run: npm run test
      - name: 🧼 Lint code
        run: npm run lint

  build:
    needs: test
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: 📦 Build Docker image
        run: docker build -t food-delivery-app .
      - name: 🔄 Push to Docker Hub
        uses: elgohr/Publish-Docker-Github-Action@master
        with:
          name: "docker-hub-username/food-delivery-app"
          username: ${{ secrets.DOCKER_HUB_USER }}
          password: ${{ secrets.DOCKER_HUB_TOKEN }}
```

