## 🔧 1️⃣ Test‑and‑Quality Playbook

| Phase | Goal | Tools & Approach | Deliverable |
|-------|------|------------------|-------------|
| **Unit** | Verify each function/route works as expected | **Jest** + **ts-jest** (Node.js), **React‑Testing‑Library** (React‑Native) | > 80 % coverage, coverage badge on PR |
| **Integration** | Test end‑to‑end flow of critical paths (signup → order → payment) | **Supertest** (NestJS), **Detox** (React‑Native) | 5‑6 end‑to‑end tests covering 3 user flows |
| **E2E** | Simulate real‑world usage (mobile + web admin) | **Cypress** (web admin) + **Detox** (mobile) | 3‑5 full‑app flows (order, cancel, track) |
| **Performance** | Ensure < 2 s response for 95 % of requests | **k6** or **Artillery** (load test) | Load‑test report, bottleneck list |
| **Security** | Catch OWASP‑top‑10 vulnerabilities | **Snyk** (dependency scanning) + **OWASP ZAP** (dynamic scan) | Security report, remediation plan |
| **CI integration** | Run all tests automatically on PR | **GitHub Actions** + **Codecov** | PR status checks, coverage badge |

### 1.1 Unit‑test skeleton (NestJS)

```ts
