## 2️⃣  Jest configuration

```json
// jest.config.js
{
  "preset": "ts-jest",
  "testEnvironment": "node",
  "roots": ["<rootDir>/src"],          // scan only src for *.spec.ts
  "moduleFileExtensions": ["ts", "js", "json"],
  "collectCoverage": true,
  "coverageDirectory": "coverage/unit",
  "coverageReporters": ["lcov", "text-summary"],
  "coverageThreshold": {
    "global": {
      "branches": 80,
      "functions": 85,
      "lines": 85,
      "statements": 85
    }
  },
  "moduleNameMapper": {
    "^@src/(.*)$": "<rootDir>/src/$1"
  }
}
```

*Why 80 %/85 %?*  
- 80 % of branches ensures every `if/else` path is exercised.  
- 85 % of functions/lines gives confidence that the core business logic is covered.  
- Adjust only if you’re sure the logic is simple enough to get a higher threshold.

